│ for the early-exit path, which correctly computes `%offset.idx + cttz(...)`.\n\nThis    │
│ change correctly targets the logic for computing the live-out value of the induction    │
│ variable on a predicated exit, which is the heart of the bug.\n\n**Final Plan:**\n1.    │
│ **Issue:** Incorrect value of induction variable used for PHI node on early loop        │
│ exit.\n2.  **Cause:** The vectorizer uses the base vector index instead of calculating  │
│ the precise scalar index of the exiting iteration.\n3.  **Fix:** Modify                 │
│ `VPlanTransforms.cpp` to ensure `getTripCountFromExit` is called to generate the        │
│ correct value for the live-out IV, and use this value in the exit PHI. The proposed     │
│ code change using `lookup` is the correct and safe way to do this."                     │
│ }                                                                                       │
